#!/bin/sh
# Base Section

# Extra Section
# Copyleft, AOSC Developers.

# Purpose of this section:
# 1. Adjustment for current system.
# 2. News and issues to be read and advised by the users.

mknod -m 600 /dev/console c 5 1 2>/dev/null || true
mknod -m 666 /dev/null c 1 3 2>/dev/null || true

echo -e "\

Welcome to AOSC OS (with the brand new Core 3.6.1)!

Core 3.6.1 fixes an issue that GNU libc (glibc) is not providing a full set
of static libraries useful for static binary productions.

This update is an development support update, users can go on with life like
it never happened.

------------------------------------------------------------------------------
Major update information.
------------------------------------------------------------------------------

Core 3.6.0 is a major update for AOSC OS Core.

For users:
	- System is possibly faster now, thanks to new optimizations applied
	  to GCC compiler and runtime libraries.

For developers:
	- GCC is updated to 6.1.0. Now using Profile Guided Optimization.
	- Included Bash developer samples/examples.
	- Added host-prefixed symlinks for GCC and Binutils.

Other change(s):
	- Marked Time Zone Data (tzdata) as a arch-neutral package.
	- Properly fixed GNU Libc C.UTF-8 support.

------------------------------------------------------------------------------

Please report any issue encountered at:

https://github.com/AOSC-Dev/aosc-os-core/issues/
"
